Global Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) Blood Flow Meter Market Insights
Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) Blood Flow Meter Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 9.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) Blood Flow Meter Market Overview
The global Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) Blood Flow Meter market is projected to experience significant growth over the next decade. The market was valued at approximately USD 220 million in 2024 and is expected to reach USD 380 million by 2034, growing at a CAGR of 5.5%. The increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases, advancements in MRI technology, and the rising demand for non-invasive diagnostic tools are key factors driving this growth. Additionally, the increasing application of MRI blood flow meters in research and healthcare facilities further boosts the market potential. The integration of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning in MRI systems to enhance diagnostic accuracy also supports market expansion.

